<h2 id="Question">Question<a class="anchor-link" href="#Question">¶</a></h2><p>If you receive a $100,000 windfall, what are the tradoffs between investing those funds immeadiately versus dollar-cost averaging the investment over time?</p>
<h2 id="Background">Background<a class="anchor-link" href="#Background">¶</a></h2><p>Dollar-cost averaging (DCA) and lump-sum investing (LSI) have long been debated. If you believe the market generally goes up, LSI allows you to gain exposure to the market as soon as possible. DCA on the otherhand, minimizes potential feelings of regret (i.e. you invest your lump sum right before a market crash).  A <a href="https://pressroom.vanguard.com/nonindexed/7.23.2012_Dollar-cost_Averaging.pdf">Vanguard study</a> concluded that "an LSI approach has outperformed a DCA approach approximately two-thirds of the time".</p>
<h2 id="Experiment">Experiment<a class="anchor-link" href="#Experiment">¶</a></h2><p>Let's imagine we come into a $100,000 windfall on any day between the funds existence (Nov 13, 2000 to Nov 28, 2016). We have two strategies:</p>
<ol>
<li>Lump-sum invest the $100,000 all at once on the date you receive the windfall.</li>
<li>Dollar-cost average the \$100,000 in 10 equal portions of \$10,000 every 30 days starting from the data of the windfall, for a total investment period of 300 days. I arbitrally chose this, because it felt good.</li>
</ol>
<p>If I had to invest a windfall in one fund it would be the Vanguard Total Stock Market Index Fund (<a href="https://personal.vanguard.com/us/funds/snapshot?FundId=0585&FundIntExt=INT">VTSAX</a>), which seeks to mimic the U.S. Stock Market.</p>
<h2 id="Assumptions">Assumptions<a class="anchor-link" href="#Assumptions">¶</a></h2><ul>
<li>Ignoring value of dollar changing over time</li>
<li>Final investment value is based on the closing price of the last day (Nov 28, 2016)</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="Getting-financial-data">Getting financial data<a class="anchor-link" href="#Getting-financial-data">¶</a></h2><p>I'm importing data from <a href="https://www.quandl.com/">Quandl</a>, a great resource for financial and economic data that feeds right into Python and <a href="http://pandas.pydata.org/">Pandas</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [1]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">quandl</span>
<span class="n">vtsax</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">quandl</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">get</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"YAHOO/FUND_VTSAX"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">vtsax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">head</span><span class="p">())</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">""</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">vtsax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">tail</span><span class="p">())</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>We'll be using Adjusted Close because it accounts for stocks splits, dividends and distribution. Let's plot the data using <a href="http://matplotlib.org/">matplotlib</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [2]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="o">%</span><span class="k">matplotlib</span> inline
<span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">matplotlib.pyplot</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">plt</span>
<span class="kn">from</span> <span class="nn">matplotlib.ticker</span> <span class="k">import</span> <span class="n">FuncFormatter</span>
<span class="kn">from</span> <span class="nn">matplotlib</span> <span class="k">import</span> <span class="n">style</span>
<span class="n">style</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">use</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'fivethirtyeight'</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">vtsax</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'Adjusted Close'</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">figsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">))</span>
<span class="n">ax</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">subplot</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">yaxis</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_major_formatter</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">FuncFormatter</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="k">lambda</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">pos</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="s1">'$</span><span class="si">{:,.0f}</span><span class="s1">'</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">format</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">)))</span> <span class="c1"># y-axis in dollars</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">title</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'VTSAX Historical Stock Price'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">ylabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'Stock Price ($)'</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>As expected. The market generally goes up. We can see the bubble in October 2007 and the crash into 2009, followed by the raging bull market (with a couple of hiccups) since then.</p>
<h2 id="Calculate-Lump-Sum">Calculate Lump Sum<a class="anchor-link" href="#Calculate-Lump-Sum">¶</a></h2><p>Let's say we invest our $100,000 windfall on anyone of those dates. How much would the investment be worth today (Nov 28, 2016)?</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [3]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">today_price</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">vtsax</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'Adjusted Close'</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="c1"># The final value of our stock (Nov 28, 2016)</span>
<span class="n">initial_investment</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">100000</span> <span class="c1"># Our $100,000 windfall</span>

<span class="n">num_stocks_bought</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">initial_investment</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">vtsax</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'Adjusted Close'</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="n">lumpsum</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">num_stocks_bought</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="n">today_price</span>

<span class="n">lumpsum</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">figsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">color</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'r'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ax</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">subplot</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">yaxis</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_major_formatter</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">FuncFormatter</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="k">lambda</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">pos</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="s1">'$</span><span class="si">{:,.0f}</span><span class="s1">'</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">format</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">)))</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">title</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Lump Sum - Today's value of $100,000 invested on date"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">ylabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'Stock Price ($)'</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">

</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>In the graph above, the x-axis represents the date made our $100,000 lump-sum investment and the y-axis is the value of that investment today.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [4]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"If we timed our lump-sum perfectetly, $100,000 invested on </span><span class="si">{}</span><span class="s2"> would be worth $</span><span class="si">{:,.2f}</span><span class="s2"> today."</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">format</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">lumpsum</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">idxmax</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">strftime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'%b </span><span class="si">%d</span><span class="s1">, %Y'</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">lumpsum</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">max</span><span class="p">()))</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">""</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Alternatively, if we invested our lump-sum at the peak of the 2007-2009 crash, $100,000 invested on </span><span class="si">{}</span><span class="s2"> would still be worth $</span><span class="si">{:,.2f}</span><span class="s2"> today."</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">format</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">lumpsum</span><span class="p">[:</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">9</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="mi">252</span><span class="p">)]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">idxmin</span><span class="p">()</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">strftime</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'%b </span><span class="si">%d</span><span class="s1">, %Y'</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">lumpsum</span><span class="p">[:</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">9</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="mi">252</span><span class="p">)]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">min</span><span class="p">()))</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="output_wrapper">
<div class="output">
<div class="output_area"><div class="prompt"></div>
<div class="output_subarea output_stream output_stdout output_text">
<pre>If we timed our lump-sum perfectetly, $100,000 invested on Oct 09, 2002 would be worth $406,177.34 today.

Alternatively, if we invested our lump-sum at the peak of the 2007-2009 crash, $100,000 invested on Oct 09, 2007 would still be worth $174,065.69 today.
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Let's run the same experiment with dollar-cost averaging now. We will invest 10 equal poritons of \$10,000 (totalling our $100,000 windfall) every 30 days, for a total investment period of 30 days.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [5]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">pandas</span> <span class="k">as</span> <span class="nn">pd</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">doDCA</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">investment</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">start_date</span><span class="p">):</span>
    <span class="c1"># gets dates of 10 investment dates (spaced 30 days apart) beginning on the day we receive our windfall</span>
    <span class="n">investment_dates_all</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">date_range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">start_date</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">periods</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">freq</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'30D'</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
    <span class="c1"># removes dates beyond the most recent data available</span>
    <span class="n">investment_dates</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">investment_dates_all</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">investment_dates_all</span> <span class="o"><</span> <span class="n">vtsax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]]</span>
    
    <span class="c1"># since not all dates will be a business day, this returns the closest buseiness day</span>
    <span class="n">closest_investment_dates</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">vtsax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">searchsorted</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">investment_dates</span><span class="p">)</span>
    
    <span class="c1"># $10,000 investement every 30 days</span>
    <span class="n">portion</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">investment</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="mf">10.0</span>
    
    <span class="c1"># gets the number of stocks purchased over the 300 day investment period</span>
    <span class="n">stocks_invested</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">sum</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">portion</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="n">vtsax</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'Adjusted Close'</span><span class="p">][</span><span class="n">closest_investment_dates</span><span class="p">])</span>
    
    <span class="c1"># adds cash value in for cash that has not yet been invested (start dates <300 days from today)</span>
    <span class="n">uninvested_dollars</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">portion</span> <span class="o">*</span> <span class="nb">sum</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">investment_dates_all</span> <span class="o">>=</span> <span class="n">vtsax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">])</span>
    
    <span class="c1"># value of stocks today</span>
    <span class="n">total_value</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">today_price</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n">stocks_invested</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">uninvested_dollars</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">total_value</span>

<span class="c1"># Generates DCA series for every initial investment date</span>
<span class="n">dca</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">pd</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Series</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">vtsax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">map</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="k">lambda</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="n">doDCA</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">initial_investment</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">)),</span> <span class="n">index</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">vtsax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Below we plot the DCA data, where the x-axis is the date we started dollar-cost averaging (and continued for 300 days in 30 day incrments from the start date, and the y-axis represents the value of the investment today.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [6]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">dca</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">figsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">color</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'b'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ax</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">subplot</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">yaxis</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_major_formatter</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">FuncFormatter</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="k">lambda</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">pos</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="s1">'$</span><span class="si">{:,.0f}</span><span class="s1">'</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">format</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">)))</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">title</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'Dollar-Cost Average - Value of $10,000 invested on date'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">ylabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'Investment Value ($)'</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>As you can see our DCA graph takes the same general shape as our lump-sum graph but is smoothed out. Any x-value in which the LSI (red) line is above the DCA (blue) value, LSI would have payed off.</p>

<div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Comparison-of-lump-sum-vs.-dollar-cost-averaging">Comparison of lump-sum vs. dollar-cost averaging<a class="anchor-link" href="#Comparison-of-lump-sum-vs.-dollar-cost-averaging">¶</a></h2><p>Both the LSI and DCA strategies have been tested for every day between Nov 13, 2000 and Nov 28, 2016.</p>
<p>Let's plot three graphs with a shared x-axis.</p>
<ul>
<li>VTSAX historical closing price</li>
<li>A LSI and DCA comparison</li>
<li>Difference between LSI and DCA as <strong>diff = (lumpsum - dca)</strong></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [8]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># Difference between lump sum and DCA</span>
<span class="n">diff</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">lumpsum</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">dca</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">fig</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">ax1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ax2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">ax3</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">plt</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">subplots</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">sharex</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="kc">True</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">figsize</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">17</span><span class="p">))</span>

<span class="c1"># VTSAX Actual</span>
<span class="n">vtsax</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'Adjusted Close'</span><span class="p">]</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">ax1</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ax1</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">yaxis</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_major_formatter</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">FuncFormatter</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="k">lambda</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">pos</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="s1">'$</span><span class="si">{:,.0f}</span><span class="s1">'</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">format</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="p">)))</span> <span class="c1"># Y axis in dollars</span>
<span class="n">ax1</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_xlabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">''</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ax1</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_title</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'VTSAX Historical Stock Price'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ax1</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_ylabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'Stock Value ($)'</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Comparison</span>
<span class="n">dca</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">ax2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">color</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'b'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">lumpsum</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">plot</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">ax</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">ax2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">color</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'r'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ax2</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">axhline</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">initial_investment</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">linestyle</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"--"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">color</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"black"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ax2</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">text</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">vtsax</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">50</span><span class="p">],</span><span class="n">initial_investment</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="mf">1.1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"Initial Investment"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ax2</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">yaxis</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_major_formatter</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">FuncFormatter</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="k">lambda</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">pos</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="s1">'$</span><span class="si">{:,.0f}</span><span class="s1">K'</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">format</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="n">e</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">)))</span> <span class="c1"># Y axis $1,000s</span>
<span class="n">ax2</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">legend</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="s2">"DCA"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"Lump-Sum"</span><span class="p">])</span>
<span class="n">ax2</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_title</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'Comparison Lump Sum vs. Dollar Cost Averaging - Value of $100K invested on date'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ax2</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_ylabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'Investment Value ($)'</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Difference</span>
<span class="n">ax3</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fill_between</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">diff</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y1</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">diff</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y2</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">color</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'red'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">where</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">diff</span><span class="o">></span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ax3</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fill_between</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">diff</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">index</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y1</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">diff</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y2</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">color</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'blue'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">where</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">diff</span><span class="o"><</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">ax3</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">yaxis</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_major_formatter</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">FuncFormatter</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="k">lambda</span> <span class="n">x</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">pos</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="s1">'$</span><span class="si">{:,.0f}</span><span class="s1">K'</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">format</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">x</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="n">e</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">)))</span> <span class="c1"># Y axis $1,000s</span>
<span class="n">ax3</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_ylabel</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'Difference ($)'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ax3</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">set_title</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'Difference (Lump Sum - Dollar Cost Average)'</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">ax3</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">legend</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="s2">"Lump-Sum > DCA"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s2">"DCA > Lump-Sum"</span><span class="p">]);</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Let's first begin by checking on what percent of days lump-sum investing investing returns more the DCA.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [9]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Lump-sum returns more than DCA </span><span class="si">%.1f%%</span><span class="s2"> of all the days"</span> <span class="o">%</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">100</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="nb">sum</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">diff</span><span class="o">></span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">diff</span><span class="p">)))</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"DCA returns more than lump-sum </span><span class="si">%.1f%%</span><span class="s2"> of all the days"</span> <span class="o">%</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">100</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="nb">sum</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">diff</span><span class="o"><</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">)</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">diff</span><span class="p">)))</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="output_wrapper">
<div class="output">
<div class="output_area"><div class="prompt"></div>
<div class="output_subarea output_stream output_stdout output_text">
<pre>Lump-sum returns more than DCA 70.0% of all the days
DCA returns more than lump-sum 30.0% of all the days
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>So <strong>70%</strong> of the time, a one-time lump-sum investment results in a higer final investment value! Nearly spot on with Vanguard's claim that lump-sum investing wins out two-thirds of the time.</p>
<p>But maybe that's not the whole story...maybe when DCA wins out it <em>really</em> wins out. Let's look at the average performance of lump-sum and DCA</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [10]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Mean difference: Average dollar improvement lump-sum returns vs. DCA: $</span><span class="si">{:,.0f}</span><span class="s2">"</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">format</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">sum</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">diff</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">diff</span><span class="p">)))</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Mean difference when lump-sum > DCA: $</span><span class="si">{:,.0f}</span><span class="s2">"</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">format</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">sum</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">diff</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">diff</span><span class="o">></span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">])</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="nb">sum</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">diff</span><span class="o">></span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">)))</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Mean difference when DCA > lump-sum: $</span><span class="si">{:,.0f}</span><span class="s2">"</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">format</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">sum</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">diff</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">diff</span><span class="o"><</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">])</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="nb">sum</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">diff</span><span class="o"><</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">)))</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="output_wrapper">
<div class="output">
<div class="output_area"><div class="prompt"></div>
<div class="output_subarea output_stream output_stdout output_text">
<pre>Mean difference: Average dollar improvement lump-sum returns vs. DCA: $3,631
Mean difference when lump-sum > DCA: $13,818
Mean difference when DCA > lump-sum: $20,116
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>This is interesting. Remember we made \$100,000 investment. So for every possible day in the last 16 years, a lump-sum investment of $100K would have returned <em>on average</em> \$3,631 more than dollar cost averaging, or 3.63%. That's substantial!</p>
<p>However, when DCA was the better strategy than lump-sum (~30% of the time), it returned $20,116 more on average, or 20.1%, compared to 13.8% when lump-sum outperformed DCA.</p>
<p>Phrased antoher way, would you rather:</p>
<ol>
<li>Have a 30% chance to earn an additional 20.1% on your initial investment, while having a 70% chance of foregoing an additional profit of 13.8% on your $100K investment.</li>
<li>Have a 70% chance to earn an additional 13.8% on your initial investment, while having a 30% chance of foregoing an additional profit of 20.1% on your \$100K investment.</li>
</ol>
<p>Option #1 being our DCA strategy (10 investment periods spaced 30 days apart) with Option #2 being our lump-sum strategy. You can use this framework to simulate other investment strategies.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Other-ways-of-looking-at-the-results...to-be-continued">Other ways of looking at the results...to be continued<a class="anchor-link" href="#Other-ways-of-looking-at-the-results...to-be-continued">¶</a></h2><p>I hope to dive more into this in the future. The averages I presented above probably don't tell the whole story. Standard deviation is a consideration in evaluating risk.</p>
<p>In retrospect, when market crashes are imminent, DCA seems to pull ahead. We obiviously can't predict a market crash, but their are indicators when a crash is more likely (i.e. trailing P/E ratios, Purchasing Managers' Index (PMI)). What if we were to bring these variables into our analysis.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [11]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">rel_area_lump_sum_wins</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">sum</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">diff</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">diff</span><span class="o">></span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">])</span> <span class="o">/</span> <span class="nb">sum</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb">abs</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">diff</span><span class="p">))</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"A measure of risk to reward of lump sum would be to take the area above where the difference is greater than zero and divide it by the total area of the deviation from zero"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">rel_area_lump_sum_wins</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="output_wrapper">
<div class="output">
<div class="output_area"><div class="prompt"></div>
<div class="output_subarea output_stream output_stdout output_text">
<pre>A measure of risk to reward of lump sum would be to take the area above where the difference is greater than zero and divide it by the total area of the deviation from zero
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class="output_area"><div class="prompt output_prompt">Out[11]:</div>
<div class="output_text output_subarea output_execute_result">
<pre>0.61561750593338926</pre>
